Data concerning the size, shape and structure of seeds not only have been used as an important tool for solving various taxonomic problems within the genus 
 Impatiens but also provide results useful for determining the impact of various environmental factors on the phenotypic variability of these species (
 Bell, Lechowicz & Schoen, 1991; 
 Argyres & Schmitt, 1991; 
 Schmitt, 1993; 
 Chmura, Csontos & Sendek, 2013; 
 Maciejewska-Rutkowska & Janczak, 2016).
